Okay, enough.

53:21.920 --> 53:24.359
We're done, Tom. All right?

53:25.600 --> 53:27.599
- What's your name?
- DS Ripley.

53:28.720 --> 53:31.399
- Justin.
- What I need you to do, Justin,

53:32.720 --> 53:34.439
I need you to back away.

53:36.720 --> 53:38.399
I can't do it.

53:39.120 --> 53:40.399
Of course you can.

53:42.600 --> 53:44.679
No, I can't. Sorry.

53:44.840 --> 53:47.079
You've already done enough tonight.

53:47.760 --> 53:49.359
I saw how you waded into that mob.

53:49.440 --> 53:52.399
That was brave.
Nobody could ask any more of you.

53:52.840 --> 53:54.159
So just...

53:55.440 --> 53:56.679
back off.

53:58.240 --> 53:59.519
Let me go.

54:02.080 --> 54:03.519
Let's say I did that,

54:04.440 --> 54:05.959
yeah, and all this carries on.

54:07.160 --> 54:08.839
Someone innocent gets hurt.

54:09.000 --> 54:11.879
- How am I supposed to live with that?
- It won't happen.

54:13.000 --> 54:14.479
It'll happen.

54:15.680 --> 54:17.559
You've made your point, Tom.
People are talking.

54:17.640 --> 54:20.559
You're all over the internet.
All over TV.

54:21.720 --> 54:24.999
- You've done what you needed to do.
- I don't want to do this.

54:32.960 --> 54:34.719
I'm a copper.

54:35.400 --> 54:36.999
We're on the same side.

54:38.560 --> 54:40.919
I don't think you're going to shoot me.

54:42.440 --> 54:44.079
Now, please.

54:45.040 --> 54:47.719
- Just back off.
- I'd love to.

54:48.720 --> 54:49.919
Please!

54:52.720 --> 54:53.759
